-I'm working on that, darling.

260
00:13:43,907 --> 00:13:46,740
Why should I trouble myself with
the pigtailed girl and Akane

261
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:51,440
Tendo when the burly
boy will do it for me?

262
00:13:51,540 --> 00:13:53,407
Amusing as this is,
you didn't think

263
00:13:53,507 --> 00:13:55,707
it was for Mr. Scaly
Green's sake, did you?

264
00:13:55,807 --> 00:13:57,040
[cackling]

265
00:13:57,140 --> 00:13:59,574
-You do know you're
crazy, don't you?

266
00:14:05,374 --> 00:14:07,240
[screaming]

267
00:14:08,307 --> 00:14:12,674
-Oh dear, I can't look.

268
00:14:12,774 --> 00:14:15,340
-Sorry, but I ain't
giving up nearly so easy.

269
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:17,774
See ya!

270
00:14:17,874 --> 00:14:19,740
-But Ranma, darling!

271
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:25,574
-Time to finish this.

272
00:14:25,674 --> 00:14:29,174
Martial Men's super special
attack-- Ring of no Return!

273
00:14:38,340 --> 00:14:40,174
[screaming]

274
00:14:40,274 --> 00:14:42,674
ANNOUNCER: Is this her one-way
ticket to being disqualified?

275
00:14:46,707 --> 00:14:48,107
-Akane!

276
00:14:48,207 --> 00:14:50,074
Let's take turns.

277
00:14:50,174 --> 00:14:51,674
-Ranma, you're here!

278
00:14:51,774 --> 00:14:54,707
-Did you think I wouldn't come?

279
00:14:54,807 --> 00:14:56,640
[inaudible]

280
00:14:56,740 --> 00:14:57,974
-I knew it!

281
00:14:58,074 --> 00:14:59,307
Here comes the pigtailed girl.

282
00:15:02,007 --> 00:15:02,640
-No fair!

283
00:15:02,740 --> 00:15:03,840
I object.

284
00:15:03,940 --> 00:15:06,640
-Refusing the substitution,
challenger Dido Kuji

285
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:09,407
calls for a ruling in the ring.

286
00:15:09,507 --> 00:15:11,240
-I'll allow it.

287
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:12,874
CROWD: He allows it!

288
00:15:12,974 --> 00:15:14,807
ANNOUNCER: And the
crowd goes wild.

289
00:15:14,907 --> 00:15:17,174
It's obvious who
their favorite is.

290
00:15:17,274 --> 00:15:19,874
Meanwhile, the pigtailed
girl takes over.

291
00:15:19,974 --> 00:15:21,007
-Sucks, don't it?

292
00:15:28,007 --> 00:15:29,474
-It's just as well.

293
00:15:29,574 --> 00:15:31,974
Our victory will be
that much the sweeter

294
00:15:32,074 --> 00:15:33,607
for the extra effort.

295
00:15:33,707 --> 00:15:38,474
This attack I'm about to unleash
may not look like very much.

296
00:15:38,574 --> 00:15:42,640
But I assure you, you're
about to be bowled over.

297
00:15:42,740 --> 00:15:45,540
Hi-ya!

298
00:15:45,640 --> 00:15:48,874
Sphere of Fury holds all
the anger and frustration

299
00:15:48,974 --> 00:15:51,274
that come from being in a club
that's such a joke, that's

300
00:15:51,374 --> 00:15:54,974
so uncool that all the
girls think you're a dweeb.

301
00:15:55,074 --> 00:15:56,940
-That is pretty mad, all right.

302
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:58,074
-Boy, I'll say.

303
00:15:58,174 --> 00:16:00,440
Even the Debate Team's
cooler than them.

304
00:16:03,974 --> 00:16:08,307
-Treasure Two,
Ribbon of Solitude!

305
00:16:08,407 --> 00:16:10,840
Ribbon of Solitude
holds all the sadness

306
00:16:10,940 --> 00:16:13,507
that comes from not having
a date on Friday night.

307
00:16:13,607 --> 00:16:16,307
So powerful a weapon
is it, a single strike

308
00:16:16,407 --> 00:16:20,074
brings forth the bitter tears
of four years of high school.

309
00:16:20,174 --> 00:16:23,407
Or six, depending on if you're
counting junior higher or not.

310
00:16:34,340 --> 00:16:37,174
-What the-- ugh.

311
00:16:37,274 --> 00:16:39,640
Ah!

312
00:16:39,740 --> 00:16:42,040
Do I get the dumb
treasure now or what?

313
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:43,774
-Oh yeah, that's right.

314
00:16:43,874 --> 00:16:45,174
I forgot.

315
00:16:45,274 --> 00:16:47,907
Furinkan High has still got a
treasure of its own we can use.

316
00:16:53,140 --> 00:16:55,207
-Now this is more like it.

317
00:16:55,307 --> 00:16:56,874
Payback's hell, ain't it?

318
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:58,074
-Ah!

319
00:16:58,174 --> 00:16:59,207
No, not--

320
00:16:59,307 --> 00:17:01,507
-And what kind of power
do those things have?

321
00:17:01,607 --> 00:17:03,574
-Club of Inscrutability.

322
00:17:03,674 --> 00:17:06,840
Comes from trying to use a
really, really cool weapon,

323
00:17:06,940 --> 00:17:10,107
but failing and having to
cause a distraction instead.

324
00:17:10,207 --> 00:17:11,140
-Sorry I asked.

325
00:17:16,807 --> 00:17:17,674
-Ah!

326
00:17:17,774 --> 00:17:19,574
What the heck are those?

327
00:17:19,674 --> 00:17:21,307
-The distraction.

328
00:17:21,407 --> 00:17:23,174
-I hope you don't
take this wrong way,

329
00:17:23,274 --> 00:17:25,440
but couldn't you have
been more creative?

330
00:17:25,540 --> 00:17:27,774
-I know you're doing
us a favor, Akane,

331
00:17:27,874 --> 00:17:30,140
but you don't have
to be so critical!

332
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:33,107
-Oh, don't be so sensitive!

333
00:17:33,207 --> 00:17:34,840
-Time to finish it for good!

334
00:17:40,274 --> 00:17:42,640
Think of this as a
token of my affection.

335
00:17:45,574 --> 00:17:47,940
-Ah!

336
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:50,940
Now what do I do?

337
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:51,481
Ranma!

338
00:17:57,007 --> 00:17:57,448
Ah!

339
00:18:03,474 --> 00:18:04,974
[screaming]

340
00:18:05,074 --> 00:18:06,340
ANNOUNCER:
[inaudible] challenger

341
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:09,840
Dido Kuji left the ring.

342
00:18:09,940 --> 00:18:15,307
Either way, it's been an
exciting match, hasn't it?

343
00:18:15,407 --> 00:18:18,907
-I-- I've got you.

344
00:18:19,007 --> 00:18:19,607
ANNOUNCER: Uh-oh.

345
00:18:19,707 --> 00:18:20,540
Uh-oh!

346
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:23,240
The pigtailed girl
is on the ropes.

347
00:18:23,340 --> 00:18:25,074
-Pigtailed girl, over here!

348
00:18:25,174 --> 00:18:26,440
Jump into my arms.

349
00:18:26,540 --> 00:18:28,340
-Thanks, I'd rather
kiss a-- whoa.

350
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:37,107
If it's gonna take a
mid-air battle to beat you,

351
00:18:37,207 --> 00:18:40,607
well then so be it!

352
00:18:40,707 --> 00:18:44,607
I've got some chestnuts and
a fire I'd like you to meet.

353
00:18:44,707 --> 00:18:47,107
-Yeah, Upward Spiral
Ribbon Defense!

354
00:18:50,174 --> 00:18:52,074
ANNOUNCER: Hello, what's this?

355
00:18:52,174 --> 00:18:54,407
The pigtailed girl's
attempting a breakthrough

356
00:18:54,507 --> 00:18:57,574
of what seems an
impenetrable defense.

357
00:18:57,674 --> 00:19:01,040
RANMA: Come out, come
out wherever you are.

358
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:03,040
-What an incredible fight.

359
00:19:03,140 --> 00:19:05,540
It's also an incredible
mess if you ask me, but--

360
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:08,540
[crowd screaming]

361
00:19:12,107 --> 00:19:12,640
-Come on!

362
00:19:12,740 --> 00:19:14,007
Come on, open up!

363
00:19:21,107 --> 00:19:21,556
Gotcha!

364
00:19:28,074 --> 00:19:29,474
-Don't do it!

365
00:19:29,574 --> 00:19:30,474
You can't.

366
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:34,940
ANNOUNCER: That's it.

367
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:35,940
That's all she wrote.

368
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:38,440
The pigtailed girl wins.

369
00:19:38,540 --> 00:19:39,940
-Woo-hoo, yeah!

370
00:19:40,040 --> 00:19:41,940
-Ranma!

371
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,007
-So, uh, what?

372
00:19:43,107 --> 00:19:44,907
You're expecting anything less?

373
00:19:45,007 --> 00:19:47,374
-Oh, no you don't!

374
00:19:47,474 --> 00:19:47,915
-Kodachi?

375
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,240
-Ranma!

376
00:19:54,340 --> 00:19:56,540
-All that's left for
me to do is step down

377
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:58,240
and collect the Sphere of Fury.

378
00:19:58,340 --> 00:20:00,307
Then, all three
treasures will be mine,

379
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:03,740
making me the queen of
martial arts gymnastics!

380
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:04,281
A-ha-ha!

381
00:20:21,107 --> 00:20:23,674
-At last, the three
treasures are ours!

382
00:20:23,774 --> 00:20:25,274
-Hey now, I object.

383
00:20:25,374 --> 00:20:26,540
ANNOUNCER: Is this it?

384
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:29,140
Have the Martial Arts Men
Team triumphed after all?

385
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:31,440
With all three treasures
now in their possession,

386
00:20:31,540 --> 00:20:33,707
it would seem to be so!

387
00:20:33,807 --> 00:20:35,540
-Now, wait a sec.

388
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:38,607
I remember reading
something about this.

389
00:20:38,707 --> 00:20:40,907
It says it's very
important for neither boys

390
00:20:41,007 --> 00:20:42,874
nor girls to own all three.

391
00:20:42,974 --> 00:20:43,974
-But why not?

392
00:20:44,074 --> 00:20:45,440
What's supposed to happen?

393
00:20:45,540 --> 00:20:46,940
-Hey, look up there.

394
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:48,640
-Martial Arts Men's
Gymnastics rules!

395
00:20:51,607 --> 00:20:54,774
Wha-- wha-- what
are those things?

396
00:20:54,874 --> 00:20:55,315
Hey!

397
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:01,840
-The Spirits of Girls
Upset because they've

398
00:21:01,940 --> 00:21:05,274
wasted their entire youth
on nothing but martial arts

399
00:21:05,374 --> 00:21:06,674
gymnastics.

400
00:21:06,774 --> 00:21:09,074
-Oh, well now I know
that you're making it up.

401
00:21:09,174 --> 00:21:10,674
-But I'm not.

402
00:21:10,774 --> 00:21:12,240
-That's it, I'm
quitting the club

403
00:21:12,340 --> 00:21:13,874
and getting myself a boyfriend.

404
00:21:13,974 --> 00:21:15,240
-Hey, me too.

405
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:16,707
-Somebody help me!

406
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:21,440
-Don't you see?

407
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:24,074
It's their way of telling
us that life without romance

408
00:21:24,174 --> 00:21:25,540
is hardly worth living!

409
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:28,174
And that it's our
duty, Ranma-- yours

410
00:21:28,274 --> 00:21:30,074
and mine-- to be happy for them.

411
00:21:30,174 --> 00:21:31,074
[sighing]

412
00:21:32,674 --> 00:21:33,115
-What?

413
00:21:33,174 --> 00:21:33,615
-I dunno.

414
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:38,040
[ribbit]

415
00:21:45,469 --> 00:21:48,869
[theme music]

416
00:23:16,966 --> 00:23:18,300
What was thought
to be a relaxing

417
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:20,933
trip to the hot springs turns
into some kind of crazy scheme

418
00:23:21,033 --> 00:23:24,466
to get men and women together
in the-- oh, wait, wait.

419
00:23:24,566 --> 00:23:25,766
Let me try that again.

420
00:23:25,866 --> 00:23:28,033
Next time, on Ranma--

